post_text:
Today the Colorado High School Activities Association released an adjusted high school sports calendar approved by the State COVID-19 Response Team. Below is a link to the new schedule. Most immediately, GVHS Cross Country teams will be allowed to begin practice 8/12. While all sports are set to be played this year, no other GVHS sports will begin until January. Many questions remain and we will be receiving more detailed information in the coming days and weeks.
Hoy, la Asociación de Actividades de la Escuela Secundaria de Colorado dio un nuevo calendario deportivo de la escuela secundaria aprobado por el Equipo de Respuesta COVID-19. A continuación hay un enlace al nuevo horario. Más inmediatamente, los equipos de GVHS Cross Country podrán comenzar a practicar 8/12. Todos los deportes se jugarán este año, pero ningún otro deporte de GVHS comenzará hasta enero. Quedan muchas preguntas y estaremos recibiendo información más detallada en los próximos días y semanas.
https://chsaanow.com/2020-08-04/chsaa-announces-2020-21-athletics-and-activities-calendar/

Your support is appreciated during this time of celebration.

post_text:
Gov. Polis has announced that he is extending the suspension of normal in-person learning at all public and private elementary and secondary schools until April 30.
GCSD 16 anticipated this and we continue to work diligently to provide distance learning and nutrition services to our students. This new format is stretching our capacities and testing our skills. It has not been without its failures, but our resolve is real and our desire to help our students and families thrive through this difficult time is true. The dedication of the GCSD 16 employees, our students, our parents, and our community have been wonderful thus far and we are confident will continue to be so to April 30th and beyond.

Hemos recogido y etiquetado todos los artículos de los lockers de GVHS . Los estudiantes/familias pueden recoger estos artículos de la oficina del Distrito en 0460 Stone Quarry Road. 970-285-5701

High School Locker Items and Athletic Order Pick-up
We have collected and tagged all hall locker items from the high school. Students/families may pick-up these items from the District office at 0460 Stone Quarry Road. 970-285-5701

Also, athletic orders and senior t-shirt orders may be picked up at the District office.

The distribution will begin Wednesday (4/1) at 3:00 and end at 4:00. Pick-up will continue from 8:00-4:00 on Thursday and Friday (4/2 and 4/3). Please call the main office to have your items brought to the drive-up area. The office number is 970-285-5701.

This is for GVHS only. We will be collecting items from middle school lockers in the next few days then move to BUE classrooms. We will announce pick-up times for these schools when we have collected and tagged all items.

post_text:
Meal distribution is still scheduled for Tuesday and Thursday from 11:00-12:30. Like last week, meals will be distributed at BUE and CFL. There will be one lane for the drive-thru area and there will also be a walk-up area. There will be no parking available at the schools. The walk-up area is for families that live close enough to the locations to walk from their homes to pick up meals. We will respect the social distancing guidelines of 6 feet apart, and we will prohibit groups of people congregating at the walk-thru area. We will be following proper protocols and recommendations from the Health Department. We cannot allow congregating and socializing. People must get their food and disperse from the area for the protection of all. Our staff will place meals directly in the cargo area of vehicles to avoid contact.

We will not be able to accommodate allergies or special dietary needs through this emergency feeding program. There WILL BE peanut products in the bags.

This is for children ages 1 to 18 years of age and students.

post_text:
After consultation with State and area health departments, the Colorado Department of Education, nearby school districts, and other authorities, Garfield County School District 16 will not be opening schools next week. The ever changing guidance we receive and quickly changing circumstances make it difficult for the experts to give us long term directions. We expect to have new instructions by the end of this week. We will send out more detailed information to our families Friday, March 20 so we all have a better idea of what to expect from the schools in the next few weeks. The District offices will be staffed on Monday to answer phone calls.

We appreciate your patience in these unprecedented times. We have many moving pieces in our school district and we intend to provide the best attention to all pieces.

We will send out more detailed information to our families Friday, March 20 so we all have a better idea of what to expect from the schools in the next few weeks. The District offices will be staffed on Monday to answer phone calls.

We appreciate your patience in these unprecedented times. We have many moving pieces in our school district and we intend to provide the best attention to all pieces.

post_text:
Después de consultar con los departamentos de salud estatales y de área, el Departamento de Educación de Colorado, los distritos escolares cercanos y otras autoridades, el Distrito Escolar del Condado de Garfield 16 no abrirá escuelas la próxima semana. La orientación siempre cambiante que recibimos y las circunstancias que cambian rápidamente dificultan que los expertos nos den instrucciones a largo plazo. Esperamos tener nuevas instrucciones para finales de esta semana. Enviaremos información más detallada a nuestras familias el viernes 20 de marzo para que todos tengamos una mejor idea de qué esperar de las escuelas en las próximas semanas.

Agradecemos su paciencia en estos tiempos sin precedentes. Tenemos muchas piezas móviles en nuestro distrito escolar y tenemos la intención de brindar la mejor atención a todas las piezas.
text:
Después de consultar con los departamentos de salud estatales y de área, el Departamento de Educación de Colorado, los distritos escolares cercanos y otras autoridades, el Distrito Escolar del Condado de Garfield 16 no abrirá escuelas la próxima semana. La orientación siempre cambiante que recibimos y las circunstancias que cambian rápidamente dificultan que los expertos nos den instrucciones a largo plazo. Esperamos tener nuevas instrucciones para finales de esta semana. Enviaremos información más detallada a nuestras familias el viernes 20 de marzo para que todos tengamos una mejor idea de qué esperar de las escuelas en las próximas semanas.

Agradecemos su paciencia en estos tiempos sin precedentes. Tenemos muchas piezas móviles en nuestro distrito escolar y tenemos la intención de brindar la mejor atención a todas las piezas.

post_text:
Piranhas are Victorious
This past weekend the Piranhas, made up of many Garfield 16 5th and 6th graders, competed in the 6th grade division of the USA Invitational Regional Championship in Mesquite, NV. They came away from the competition as the Champions, defeating a Utah team that has been undefeated for four years. Moreover, GVMS’s own Bryson Whitman was selected as Player of the Game.
The Piranhas are coached by Head coach, Mike Johnson,and assisted by Andrew Terrazas, Klayton Castanzo, Mike Mendoza. Thank you to the coaches and the community for supporting these kids. Way to go Piranhas.

post_text:
Hello this is a message from the Center For Family Learning. Today at approximately 8:45 am our school was put in a lockout mode due to a situation occurring in the vicinity of the school. While no threats were made against the school or students it was determined students and staff would be safer if no one was allowed to enter of leave the building. At that time Parachute Police were responding to the scene. The school was in lockout for about eight minutes. The school was taken off of lockout after Police deemed it was safe to do so.
Due to the short span of the lockout we were not able to send a voice message to inform parents we were in a lockout before the lockout ended.
Thank you to our Parachute Police Department for their response and help.

post_text: Did you know being thankful is actually good for you? Many recent studies have shown being thankful has mental, social, and even physical benefits. Studies reveal having an attitude of gratitude can help us in many ways from getting better sleep to having more friends. Thankful people have improved self-esteem and cope better in difficult times. They attract more friends, experience fewer physical ailments, and have a general better sense of well-being. So it is good we get this chance to take some time to be thankful. It can actually improve our lives. Take care over the holiday Cardinal Family. We wish everyone a safe and happy time of thanksgiving.

We'll be serving muffins, applesauce, juice, and milk on September 7, 2018 at 7:30am. Grandparents are also invited to stay for their class CREW. The class CREW will end at 8:05am.

Permission forms and reservations must be returned to the BUE office by 4 September. Breakfast cost is $2.75. PLEASE PREPAY IF POSSIBLE. YOU CAN SEND IN THE MONEY WITH YOUR CHILD. Forms are available at the office or copy the one below:

BUE Grandparents' Breakfast
Name(s) of those attending____________________________
_________________________________________________
Student___________________________________________
How many Attending________
Parent signature____________________________________
$ AMOUNT PAID______________________

post_text: Tuesday will be another first day for most of our students and teachers, but for some of our students and teachers it will be a first - first day. For our seniors and retirees it will be a last first day. Whether it is their first, middle or last, parents too will go through the joys and concerns of this first day. For all of us it be time of new opportunities and fresh starts. Here's to a wonderful year of active minds and helping hearts.

Thursday, August 16 from 5:30-6:30 we will be providing a welcome and informational night for students and families new to Grand Valley High School. post_text:
Information for Parents and Guardians of Bea Underwood Elementary Students:

*New student registration day is Friday, August 10, 2018 9:00am-4:00pm

*Back-to-School Meet-n-Greet will be Monday, August 20th from 3:00-5:00 pm. Come enjoy frosty root beer floats served by Mrs Clark and Mrs Frees then meet your teacher and tour the school.

*First day of school is August 21, 2018

*Thank you to Garfield #16 for providing our kids with their school supplies. The only items students will need to bring to school are a backpack and tennis shoes for PE.

*Our School hours are Tuesday-Friday 7:30am-3:40pm

*While we provide free breakfast and lunch to all students, it is important families fill out the free and reduced paperwork that will be sent home on the first day of school. If we do not get this paperwork back it could jeopardize the free program. Thank you!

Please see our district website for up to date information. garco16.org

post_text: We are happy to announce the Garfield 16 School District Board and administration have approved the use of general fund money to purchase school supplies for students in preschool through eighth grade. Students attending the Center for Family Learning, Bea Underwood Elementary, and Grand Valley Middle School will be provided school supplies for the 2018-2019 school year.

Grand Valley Middle School added 13 new photos to the album: Crew Olympics: Opening Ceremonies Sept. 1st — in Parachute, Colorado.
September 1, 2017 · Parachute, CO ·

Our motto of "We are Crew, not Passengers" instills a sense of responsibility, participation and cooperation among individuals and the student body to build a better school community. We are committed to the inclusion and action in the service of self and others. EVERY kid has a place at GVMS!
